</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="CA01481569B2F09216EC03A181FB8E10" pageId="null" pageNumber="534" type="description">
<paragraph id="8180FACAA4459AF7BFE87E0415F816FD" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="58DF39586A8D59903C75C0E95E9622F9" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Convallaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="534" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflorum">
<emphasis id="E684263711B2D6E59BAE1CB96183303F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">P. multiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr.2) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="F70D32F624FD32129B08CB4DA20C9CE1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">
Stengel mit scharfen Kanten; 
<normalizedToken id="DD5D5F23953540051D42A6E25C7D1B20" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Blueten</normalizedToken>
fast immer einzeln, 
<normalizedToken id="B5561AAA79DA3116397FE1D86F09F43D" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">ueber</normalizedToken>
dem Fruchtknoten nicht verengt; 
<normalizedToken id="ADFA540281FE5F3D57C02BD6EFADAF04" originalValue="Staubfäden" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Staubfaeden</normalizedToken>
kahl. -
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="9ACC24D16FAD9D446F5AFF063F9347B9" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="5FAA81E09E2A3BB8C32BA66B25DF8726" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="45784D8CA06E1C7E668FECA31CF52EE9" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="E95F2E0E7AAE9A4C6D7548818699A14D" originalValue="früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">frueher</normalizedToken>
Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="436D933FD6DABD6AE905CB4EEC806342" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="34DD69B9D9543373B9B70AB7CC285748" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="295A1378E859C40BCECEBE9BAE1FD858" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">20:</emphasis>
Material aus Skandinavien (
<normalizedToken id="99ED605DCDCF88B9A29FD14671FDEC2B" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="AB8F6B34187C0255A20B2EE0C9C29C5D" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1942b), aus Schweden und Finnland (Suomalainen 1947), aus Ungarn (
<normalizedToken id="B670722186DB42BCB515B6FBD8612653" originalValue="Pólya" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Polya</normalizedToken>
1950), aus dem 
<normalizedToken id="3E73FB929309C5C84D8B51A3C89919E6" originalValue="Elsaß" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Elsass</normalizedToken>
(Gagnieu et al. aus 
<normalizedToken id="C878DB1AEC7F40A6380F4F55FA7AAF2C" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="036FF3DDC9A2A315EB19E9AD172593F3" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1961). 
<emphasis id="EF4AE8668054C230369DF0CDF3AA31BB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="074E4209C1FFA8BB06846FBCAD1DF53F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">26, 28, 30:</emphasis>
Material aus 
<normalizedToken id="F858FC3C2CEA55256124583CD13870ED" originalValue="Großbritannien" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Grossbritannien</normalizedToken>
(Maude 1939Maude 1940).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1710CA84A1B2C1B0EA5214E2B8274BCA" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="9D2DE1D1F13E6F70FAD436676D58CEAA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin, montan und subalpin. Trockene, lockere, humose bis steinige, kalkhaltige bis saure 
<normalizedToken id="B031887904905112CB334F7FA66689B5" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Boeden</normalizedToken>
. Lichte Trockenwald- und Trockenbuschgesellschaften, Trockenwiesen, Felsgesimse, 
<normalizedToken id="575132289542DEA6484D78AF507EFCAA" originalValue="Geröllhalden" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Geroellhalden</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D165776FEA9C4FCFE71AE3E72DD76454" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="2F1CCAC9D47D7619347A5DE6D60CD013" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Verbreitung. Eurasiatische Pflanze:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B0C7674D4A98755DED1799A42D8A6A8E" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
(ohne Arktis); Nordwestafrika; durch Asien, vor allem zwischen 50 und 55° NB, 
<normalizedToken id="2A809753ABBBA46C209DA847114E70D3" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis ins Amurgebiet; Zentralasien (Kasachstan), Japan, 
<normalizedToken id="9C7B1BC69619347042DC0E6485A9AB80" originalValue="Südchina" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Suedchina</normalizedToken>
. Verbreitungskarte von Meusel (1964). - Im Gebiet verbreitet, ziemlich 
<normalizedToken id="40C62EF8B6D4D9B114937D902FCF5DC7" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8AC95821BC3B94B9FCFB57834356865B" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="F84206E1CB83E700C44CC64655FEFE9C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Neuerdings wird 
<normalizedToken id="1EA4B87277E3329E9ED76340BD597C91" originalValue="für" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">fuer</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="12F43A6A3E5AC09E1F721D13332BBC81" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Polygonatum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="534" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinale">
<emphasis id="25AB7926F698EE05F7464A937EA61F43" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">P. officinale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auch der Name 
<taxonomicName id="EF232A4D7EBD4BA060499F56C9D2DA90" authority="(Miller) Druce" authorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityName="Miller" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Anthoxanthum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="534" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="odoratum">
<emphasis id="D49E8E0224EE111AAEEA04A51BBA70ED" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="534">P. odoratum</emphasis>
(Miller) Druce
</taxonomicName>
verwendet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
